The `line-height: 1` on the number means the line-height equals the font-size (80px). But fonts have internal leading/ascender space. 

The "01" glyph's top edge sits lower than the "About" glyph's top edge because of their different font metrics. content.text:
All four sections (01 About, 02 Manager README, 03 Career, 04 Contact) now have their section numbers and headings visually aligned at the top.

The fix was a single change in `pages/index.js` at line 350: changed `margin-top: -0.075em` to `margin-top: 0.075em` on `.ed-section-title`. The negative margin was pulling the heading text above the section number's visual top. The positive value pushes it down to compensate for the different font sizes (80px number vs 44.8px title) having different amounts of internal whitespace above their glyphs.
